<br>
The reason I was there that day was as follows: A group of guildies had been to hate for some quest stuff and as we were breaking up the person boxing our cleric noticed that he was only missing 1% exp to ding, so we thought it would be nice to ding him. We zoned into HoH and there were no one at GY at the time, so we were going to pull to there as he had to log ASAP. Right before we were going to pull a druid pulled a quad there (WE female, don’t remember the name). I thought well ok that’s np, I'll pull two (can't pull less without FD, harmony etc.) and keep one rooted and snared while kiting the other (easily doable) and be out of there quickly. So we pulled and things were going according to plan when suddenly a 3rd is trained on us (no we didn't aggro it by accident as the 4 others at the 6 spawn right in front of ZI were pulled by the druid prior, and the 2 front mobs were not up). Ok, I can CC that too np. Then a 2nd druid shows up (halfing male) with some mobs and begin to kite. At this point is getting kind of crowded, but as our mob is almost dead we decide to finish it. Then out of the blue, at least 2 other mobs are trained into GY and aggro's on us. At this point I’m CC’ing 4 mobs while kiting 1, so we decide to zone without killing the one we're kiting. The cleric apparently rooted a mob right on Rynnia by accident, which he apologised for and offered a rez.<br>
<br>
After this we zoned back in, killed one of the front mobs that had spawned alone, by root nuking it outside of the GY, right of the ZI. The cleric dinged and logged, and I moved to a basement to quad.<br>
<br>
That’s basically what happened. Setting up camp / quadding in the GY area is an extremely bad idea, especially now where HoH is much more crowded. Just say no…<br>
